article.headline: Gonzaga 103, Lewis-Clark St. 61
article.story: SPOKANE, Wash. -- Elias Harris recorded game highs of 19 points and nine rebounds to lead Gonzaga to a 103-61 win over Lewis-Clark State on Thursday night. Six players scored in double figures for the Bulldogs (5-5). Mathis Monninghoff had season highs of five 3-pointers and 15 points while Kelly Olynyk added a career-high 14 points, Robert Sacre 13, Sam Dower 12 and David Stockton 10. Donte Roberts led the Warriors (7-2), an NAIA Division I team, with 12 points. Lewis-Clark State listed the game as an exhibition and will not count the loss on their record. Gonzaga snapped a three-game losing streak despite losing leading scorer Steven Gray in the first half due to a toe injury. The Bulldogs shot a season-high 60.7 percent from the field. Lewis-Clark State shot 32.3 percent, a season low for a Gonzaga opponent.
